                                        <h2>Community - Based Mature Grade 12 Program</h2>
                                        
                                        <p>Long Plain First Nation has had a Mature Grade 12 program operating on reserve since 2000.  We have had academic partnerships with Morris MacDonald School Division, The Collegiate, University of Winnipeg and most recently, with Yellowquill College.  </p>
                                        
                                        <p>We accept adult learners who are 19 years of age and older and is open to any individual whether they live on reserve or off reserve.  Transcripts and diplomas are awarded through the College.  Our Tribal Members receive a $200.00 monthly stipend from Arrowhead Development Corporation Incorporated.</p>
                                        
                                        <p>Classes are now held at the Rufus Prince Building. Transportation is provided for the students through the Arrowhead Development Corp. Inc.  </p>
                                        
                                        <div class="divider divider-center"><i class="icon-circle"></i></div>
                                        <h2>Community - Based Business Certificate Program</h2>
                                        
                                        <p>Long Plain First Nation went into a partnership venture with Yellowquill College to deliver a Business Certificate program for the 2014/2015 academic year.  This is a pilot project for this year only.  The instructor is Sheila Cole.  There were 25 students enrolled for this program which is offered at the old store building located near the #305 gas bar.  Transportation is provided for these learners through the Arrowhead Development Corp. Ltd.</p>
                                        
                                        <div class="divider divider-center"><i class="icon-circle"></i></div>
                                        <h2>The White Buffalo Program</h2>
                                        
                                        <div class="divider divider-center"><i class="icon-circle"></i></div>
                                        <h2>Regular High School Graduation Incentive Program</h2>
                                        
                                        <p>The White Buffalo and the teachings associated to this sacred being is held in reverence amongst the Anishinabe Nations of Turtle Island.  The White Buffalo represents for many – all the good gifts the Creator has given our Nation.  The White Buffalo indicates moments in time when we experience optimism, abundance, and good fortune.  It affirms that our prayers are being answered and indicates that our prophecies are fulfilled.  </p>
                                        
                                        <p>For many, the White Buffalo Teachings encourage us to be mindful of our past and to be hopeful about our future and that the Creator has given our Nation teachings, ethics, and moral codes to govern our daily public and private lives.  Included are the seven grandfather and grandmother philosophies and these are represented by our animal relatives:</p>
                                        
                                        <p>RESPECT – Buffalo, LOVE – Eagle, COURAGE – Bear, HONESTY – Sabe, WISDOM – Beaver, HUMILITY – Wolf, TRUST – Turtle</p>
                                        
                                        <p>It is in the name of this scared teacher, The White Buffalo, that this graduation incentive is awarded to those who are most nearest and dearest to our hearts, and that we are awe-inspired and proud of our Regular High School Grade Twelve Graduates.  </p>
                                        
                                        <p>It is imperative that our Nation support the endeavors and acknowledge the good deeds that our young citizens have achieved.  In spite of the struggles and hurdles that these young individuals have had to overcome socially, academically, and personally, they hung on and they have risen above those obstacles and barriers and have come out victorious.  </p>
                                        
                                        <p>This expression of gratitude will continue as long as the Long Plain First Nation has means to do so and is able to contribute to this worthwhile cause.   Fortunately, our community has been enjoying expanding prosperity and with this prosperity, it is essential that we encourage our graduates to seek a higher level of learning and hopefully, they will come back and offer their skills and expertise for future endeavors.  By supporting our children to stay in the regular school system, our Long Plain First Nation regular high school graduates are now deemed role models who have responsibility, as they are paving the path for those who will follow.</p>
                                        
                                        <div class="divider divider-center"><i class="icon-circle"></i></div>
                                        <h2>Incentive Awards</h2>
                                        
                                        
                                        <p>1. The Arrowhead Development Corporation will offer $1,000.00 as an incentive award on behalf of the Long Plain First Nation and its membership to all regular Grade Twelve High School Graduates, regardless of residence.</p>
                                        
                                        <div class="divider divider-center"><i class="icon-circle"></i></div>
                                        <h2>On-Reserve Graduates Assistance</h2>
                                        
                                            <p>2. The Long Plain First Nation School will offer a limit of $300.00 in assistance as a contribution of costs associated with pictures, attire, rings, and any other graduation expenses.</p>
                                            
                                            <p>3. The Long Plain First Nation School will pay for any graduation fees required by the high school.</p>
                                        
                                        <div class="divider divider-center"><i class="icon-circle"></i></div>
                                        <h2>Off-Reserve Graduates Assistance</h2>
                                        
                                        
                                            <p>4. The Long Plain First Nation School will offer a limit of $300.00 in assistance as a contribution of costs associated with pictures, attire, rings, and any other graduation expenses.</p>
                                            
                                            <p>5. The Long Plain First Nation School will pay for any graduation fees required by the high school.</p>
                                        
                                        <div class="divider divider-center"><i class="icon-circle"></i></div>
                                        <h2>Other Awards</h2>
                                        
                                        
                                            <p>6. The Prairie Rose Award – The Arrowhead Development Corporation will offer an award of $200.00 to the graduate who has achieved the highest academic grade point average.  Official high school transcripts should be requested from the high schools.</p>
                                            
                                            <p>7. The Mikinak Award - The Arrowhead Development Corporation will offer an award of $200.00 to the graduate who has achieved perfect attendance in the last school year:  this award may vary from year to year.</p>
                                        
                                            <p>8. The White Buffalo Award - The Arrowhead Development Corporation will offer an award of $200.00 to the graduate who has displayed qualities o congeniality within the community among peers, with education staff, and in high schools.  This would require support letters from peers, community, and high school.</p>
                                        
                                            <p>9. The Thunderbird Award - The Arrowhead Development Corporation will offer an award of $200.00 to the graduate who has demonstrated excellence in high school sports activities.</p>
                                        
                                            <p>10. The Wolf Award - The Arrowhead Development Corporation will offer an award of $200.00 to the graduate who has achieved a grade twelve diploma in spite of any disability.</p>
                                        
